ifies-dans-le-grand-est-dont-huit-en-alsace|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Three family members were hospitalised in [[Nancy, France|Nancy]], a father and his son, aged 50 and 23, and the girl-friend of the 50-year-old patient, all from the department of [[Aisne]].<ref name=\":36\">{{cite web|url=https://www.estrepublicain.fr/edition-nancy-et-agglomeration/2020/03/02/coronavirus-deux-premiers-cas-hospitalises-a-nancy|title=Nancy. Coronavirus : un troisi\u00e8me cas av\u00e9r\u00e9 \u00e0 Nancy|website=estrepublicain.fr|language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302185634/https://www.estrepublicain.fr/edition-nancy-et-agglomeration/2020/03/02/coronavirus-deux-premiers-cas-hospitalises-a-nancy|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== Guadeloupe ====\n{{Main| 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Guadeloupe}}\n\n==== Hauts-de-France ====\nAs of 2 March 67 people<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/sante-sciences/coronavirus-un-nouveau-deces-en-france-191-cas-de-contamination-confirmes-1583176452|title=Coronavirus : un nouveau d\u00e9c\u00e8s en France, 191 cas de contamination confirm\u00e9s|date=2 March 2020|website=France Bleu|language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302193947/https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/sante-sciences/coronavirus-un-nouveau-deces-en-france-191-cas-de-contamination-confirmes-1583176452|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> were infected by COVID-19 in the [[Hauts-de-France]] region. This figure, the highest in France, was linked to a major cluster originating in the city of [[Creil]], in the [[Oise]], whose source remains unknown. The five departments of Hauts-de-France now each had at least one proven case of people infected by the coronavirus. In [[Aisne]] and [[Pas-de-Calais]], spared by the epidemic until 1 March, the authorities confirmed the presence of patients with COVID-19, except the [[Nord (French department)|Nord]] where hospitalisations without local infections had taken place.\n\nSome days before, on 26 February, a man died overnight after being rushed to a Paris hospital from [[Creil]] where he was hospitalised for 6 days in [[Intensive care unit|ICU]] in serious condition, bringing the total death toll in the country to two at that time.<ref name=\":13\" /><ref name=\":16\" /> On 2 March, it was announced the second death in [[Hauts-de-France]] and the third at the national level, a woman of 89 \"''diagnosed post-mortem''\" at the hospital of [[Compi\u00e8gne]]. She had other serious pre-existing conditions.<ref name=\"auto\" />\n\n==== \u00cele-de-France ====\nOn 25 February, a young woman returned from China was hospitalised in the [[Bichat\u2013Claude Bernard Hospital]], Paris but showed signs of recovery and was out of hospital on 26 February.<ref name=\":7\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2020/02/25/direct-coronavirus-loms-evoque-un-risque-de-pandemie-pour-la-premiere-fois,8754380.php|title=[DIRECT] DIRECT. Coronavirus : deux nouveaux cas de coronavirus en France|website=ladepeche.fr|language=fr|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"francebleu1582653755\">{{cite web|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/sante-sciences/coronavirus-deux-nouveaux-cas-en-france-annonce-le-directeur-general-de-la-sante-1582653755|title=Coronavirus : deux nouveaux cas en France annonce le directeur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral de la Sant\u00e9|date=25 February 2020|website=France Bleu|language=fr|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226061355/https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/sante-sciences/coronavirus-deux-nouveaux-cas-en-france-annonce-le-directeur-general-de-la-sante-1582653755|archive-date=26 February 2020|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":3\" />\n\nOn 28 February, an infected person from the [[Val-d'Oise]], returning from Italy was hospitalised in Bichat\u2013Claude Bernard Hospital, Paris. He was working for an exterior employee of [[Charles de Gaulle Airport]].<ref name=\"francetvinfo3843241\">{{cite web|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/sante/maladie/coronavirus/direct-covid-19-quelque-40-pays-desormais-concernes-les-etats-unis-se-preparent-a-une-propagation-du-virus_3843241.html|title=DIRECT. Covid-19 : le nombre de cas confirm\u00e9s en France passe de 18 \u00e0 38, annonce le ministre de la Sant\u00e9|date=27 February 2020|website=Franceinfo|language=fr|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":27\">{{cite news|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/economie/article/2020/02/28/a-roissy-et-a-orly-adp-n-a-pas-decele-de-cas-de-contamination-parmi-les-personnels_6031191_3234.html|title=Un premier cas de coronavirus d\u00e9tect\u00e9 parmi les personnels de Roissy-Charles-de-Gaulle|date=28 February 2020|work=Le Monde|access-date=29 February 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229165023/https://www.lemonde.fr/economie/article/2020/02/28/a-roissy-et-a-orly-adp-n-a-pas-decele-de-cas-de-contamination-parmi-les-personnels_6031191_3234.html|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On the same day, {{interlanguage link|H\u00f4pital Tenon|fr}}, which had received a patient from the Oise before he had been diagnosed, announced that it had been directly affected by the coronavirus with three infected medical personnel.<ref name=\"leparisien8269890\">{{cite web|url=http://www.leparisien.fr/societe/coronavirus-3-personnels-soignants-contamines-a-paris-a-l-hopital-tenon-29-02-2020-8269890.php|title=Coronavirus : 3 personnels soignants contamin\u00e9s \u00e0 Paris \u00e0 l'h\u00f4pital Tenon|last=Mari|first=Elsa |date=29 February 2020|website=Le Parisien|language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302191444/http://www.leparisien.fr/societe/coronavirus-3-personnels-soignants-contamines-a-paris-a-l-hopital-tenon-29-02-2020-8269890.php|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nTwo cases of Coronavirus had been identified in [[Seine-Saint-Denis]] in [[Montreuil, Seine-Saint-Denis|Montreuil]] in the same family, a father and his child, on 2 March.<ref name=\"francebleu1583145133\">{{cite web|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/sante-sciences/coronavirus-en-seine-saint-denis-des-enfants-ne-sont-plus-accueillis-dans-un-college-de-montreuil-1583145133|title=Coronavirus en Seine-Saint-Denis : deux cas identifi\u00e9s dans une famille de Montreuil|date=2 March 2020|website=France Bleu|language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302191440/https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/sante-sciences/coronavirus-en-seine-saint-denis-des-enfants-ne-sont-plus-accueillis-dans-un-college-de-montreuil-1583145133|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== Martinique ====\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Martinique}}\n\n==== Mayotte ====\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Mayotte}}\n\n==== Normandy ====\nOn 27 February, a doctor from the Rouen University Hospital was declared a positive carrier of COVID-19 and was confined to his home, after a professional journey to [[Munich]].<ref name=\":22\">{{cite web|url=https://www.paris-normandie.fr/actualites/societe/sante/un-cas-de-coronavirus-confirme-pres-de-rouen-un-professionnel-de-sante-confine-chez-lui-EA16434473|title=Un cas de coronavirus confirm\u00e9 pr\u00e8s de Rouen : un professionnel de sant\u00e9 confin\u00e9 chez lui|website=paris-normandie.fr|language=fr|access-date=28 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228180806/https://www.paris-normandie.fr/actualites/societe/sante/un-cas-de-coronavirus-confirme-pres-de-rouen-un-professionnel-de-sante-confine-chez-lui-EA16434473|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A second case of coronavirus was confirmed in Normandy on 2 March. He is a French resident in [[Eure]]. He was hospitalised at the Rouen University Hospital.<ref name=\"auto5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/societe/coronavirus-un-deuxieme-cas-en-normandie-1583162276|title=Coronavirus : un deuxi\u00e8me cas en Normandie|date=2 March 2020|website=France Bleu|language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302191740/https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/societe/coronavirus-un-deuxieme-cas-en-normandie-1583162276|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== New Aquitaine ====\nAfter news of the first infected individuals in Europe had been released during the first wave of coronavirus in France,<ref name=\":9\" /> three new patients were declared COVID-19 positive in February a patient in [[Bordeaux]], hospitalised at the Bordeaux University Hospital, returned from a stay in Italy in a city affected by coronavirus, a soldier from [[Rochefort, Charente-Maritime]], who has had contacts with people from the Creil air base in the Oise, hospitalised in [[Poitiers]], and a woman from [[Mont-de-Marsan]] was also in contact with grouped cases in Creil, hospitalised in [[Bordeaux]].<ref name=\"francetvinfo1793211\">{{cite web|url=https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/nouvelle-aquitaine/charente-maritime-homme-contamine-coronavirus-ete-transporte-au-chu-poitiers-1793211.html|title=Charente-Maritime : un homme contamin\u00e9 par le coronavirus a \u00e9t\u00e9 transport\u00e9 au CHU de Poitiers|website=France 3 Nouvelle-Aquitaine|language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301120015/https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/nouvelle-aquitaine/charente-maritime-homme-contamine-coronavirus-ete-transporte-au-chu-poitiers-1793211.html|archive-date=1 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== Occitania ====\nThree cases were declared in Occitania in February, all in Montpellier. A man who recently returned from Italy was diagnosed on 27 February,<ref name=\":19\">{{cite web|url=https://www.midilibre.fr/2020/02/27/coronavirus-un-premier-cas-avere-a-montpellier,8760787.php|title=Coronavirus: un premier cas av\u00e9r\u00e9 \u00e0 Montpellier|website=midilibre.fr|language=fr|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> followed the next day by his wife and a 41-year-old man recently returned from [[Emilia-Romagna]].<ref name=\":32\">{{cite web|url=https://actu.fr/occitanie/montpellier_34172/coronavirus-montpellier-deux-autres-cas-averes-dont-lepouse-malade-deja-infecte_31832600.html|title=Coronavirus \u00e0 Montpellier : deux autres cas av\u00e9r\u00e9s, dont l'\u00e9pouse du malade d\u00e9j\u00e0 infect\u00e9|website=actu.fr|language=fr|access-date=28 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228204845/https://actu.fr/occitanie/montpellier_34172/coronavirus-montpellier-deux-autres-cas-averes-dont-lepouse-malade-deja-infecte_31832600.html|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On 1 March, the two children of the couple were hospitalised and one was COVID-19 positive.<ref name=\"francebleu1583167955\">{{cite web|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/sante-sciences/coronavirus-l-enfant-contamine-a-montpellier-a-tres-peu-de-symptomes-1583167955|title=Coronavirus : l'enfant contamin\u00e9 \u00e0 Montpellier a tr\u00e8s peu de sympt\u00f4mes|date=2 March 2020|website=France Bleu|language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302181749/https://www.francebleu.fr/infos/sante-sciences/coronavirus-l-enfant-contamine-a-montpellier-a-tres-peu-de-symptomes-1583167955|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On 2 March, two new cases were announced there: a 31-year-old man and his 29-year-old wife, also back from [[Emilia-Romagna]].<ref name=\"ladepeche8768545\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2020/03/02/direct-coronavirus-deux-nouveaux-cas-en-occitanie-plus-de-3000-morts-dans-le-monde,8768545.php|title= Coronavirus: 191 cas confirm\u00e9s en France, un nouveau cas \u00e0 Montpellier|website=ladepeche.fr| language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302160920/https://www.ladepeche.fr/2020/03/02/direct-coronavirus-deux-nouveaux-cas-en-occitanie-plus-de-3000-morts-dans-le-monde,8768545.php|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> One day later, a 70-year-old man from the village of [[Boisset-et-Gaujac]] in the Gard was hospitalised in [[N\u00eemes]].<ref name=\":38\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2020/03/03/direct-coronavirus-trois-morts-en-france-nous-sommes-en-terre-inconnue-dit-loms,8771171.php|title= Coronavirus: un quatri\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s en France, plus de 200 cas dans le pays|website=ladepeche.fr|language=fr|access-date=3 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304144617/https://www.ladepeche.fr/2020/03/03/direct-coronavirus-trois-morts-en-france-nous-sommes-en-terre-inconnue-dit-loms,8771171.php|archive-date=4 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 March it was identified in [[N\u00eemes]] one case coming from the Mulhouse Megachurch event (mid-february). This is this case which helped identify the Mulhouse megachurch issue.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.franceculture.fr/societe/covid-19-le-nombre-de-cas-au-rassemblement-evangelique-de-mulhouse-largement-sous-estime |title=Covid-19 : le nombre de cas au rassemblement \u00e9vang\u00e9lique de Mulhouse largement sous-estim\u00e9 |publisher=Franceculture.fr |date=2020-03-28 |accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n==== Pays de la Loire ====\nA 58-year-old woman, a general practitioner, tested positive for coronavirus and was hospitalised on 27 February at the Nantes University Hospital. Hers was the first confirmed case in the [[Pays de la Loire]] region. She lives near [[Compi\u00e8gne]], in the Oise department, where a dozen cases had already been identified. On 13 February she had seen a patient who was later hospitalised in an intensive care unit in Amiens.<ref name=\"www6755160\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sante/virus/coronavirus/direct-coronavirus-les-contaminations-ralentissent-en-chine-18-cas-en-france-6755160|title=Coronavirus: 38 cas d\u00e9sormais confirm\u00e9s en France|last=Reuters|first=avec AFP et|date=27 February 2020|website=Ouest-France|language=fr|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"www6756083\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/pays-de-la-loire/nantes-44000/nantes-un-premier-cas-de-coronavirus-hospitalise-au-chu-6756083|title=Coronavirus: un premier cas de contamination hospitalis\u00e9 au CHU de Nantes|last=Ouest-France|date=27 February 2020|website=Ouest-France|language=fr|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 March, four people were hospitalised at the Angers University Hospital for cases of coronavirus.<ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web|url=https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/pays-de-la-loire/maine-et-loire/angers/coronavirus-quatre-patients-hospitalises-au-chu-angers-sont-tres-peu-symptomatiques-1793601.html|title=Coronavirus : les quatre patients hospitalis\u00e9s au CHU d'Angers sont tr\u00e8s peu \"symptomatiques\"|website=France 3 Pays de la Loire|language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302193333/https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/pays-de-la-loire/maine-et-loire/angers/coronavirus-quatre-patients-hospitalises-au-chu-angers-sont-tres-peu-symptomatiques-1793601.html|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The first case was detected on 28 February; a 27-year-old woman from the [[Sarthe]] declared herself to the SAMU centre 15 after a stay in [[Milan]] in Italy. Three other cases have since been detected in [[Mayenne]] and [[Maine-et-Loire]]. They were infected by a patient from [[Brest, France|Brest]].<ref name=\":25\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/pays-de-la-loire/angers-49000/coronavirus-trois-cas-averes-hospitalises-au-chu-d-angers-6757664|title=Coronavirus. Trois cas av\u00e9r\u00e9s hospitalis\u00e9s au CHU d'Angers|last=Ouest-France|date=28 February 2020|website=Ouest-France|language=fr|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229120927/https://www.ouest-france.fr/pays-de-la-loire/angers-49000/coronavirus-trois-cas-averes-hospitalises-au-chu-d-angers-6757664|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== Provence-Alpes-C\u00f4te d'Azur ====\nThe first case of the [[Provence-Alpes-C\u00f4te d'Azur]] region was announced on 28 February. A young woman from [[Cannes]] was infected after a journey in [[Milan]].<ref name=\":23\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nicematin.com/sante/un-premier-cas-de-coronavirus-confirme-dans-les-alpes-maritimes-471495|title=Un premier cas de coronavirus confirm\u00e9 dans les Alpes-Maritimes|date=28 February 2020|website=Nice-Matin|language=fr|access-date=28 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228174333/https://www.nicematin.com/sante/un-premier-cas-de-coronavirus-confirme-dans-les-alpes-maritimes-471495|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> One day later three new cases were hospitalised, two French vacationers returned from a risk zone and an Italian tourist.<ref name=\"nicematin472403\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nicematin.com/sante/trois-nouveaux-malades-du-coronavirus-ce-samedi-dans-les-alpes-maritime-472403|title=Trois nouveaux malades du coronavirus ce samedi dans les Alpes-Maritime|date=29 February 2020|website=Nice-Matin|language=fr|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229144248/https://www.nicematin.com/sante/trois-nouveaux-malades-du-coronavirus-ce-samedi-dans-les-alpes-maritime-472403|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Two new cases appeared during the weekend of 29 February and 1 March: a 15-year-old adolescent and a 23-year-old woman.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/provence-alpes-cote-d-azur/alpes-maritimes/nice/coronavirus-enfant-trois-ans-contamine-nice-point-situation-1794029.html|title=Coronavirus : un enfant de trois ans contamin\u00e9 \u00e0 Nice, le point sur la situation|website=France 3 Provence-Alpes-C\u00f4te d'Azur|language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302194919/https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/provence-alpes-cote-d-azur/alpes-maritimes/nice/coronavirus-enfant-trois-ans-contamine-nice-point-situation-1794029.html|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On 2 March, a seventh case was announced, a 3-year-old girl.<ref name=\"auto1\" />\n\nOn 29 February Monaco announced its first COVID-19 case, a man who was admitted to the [[Princess Grace Hospital Centre]], then transferred to the Nice University Hospital in France.<ref name=\":37\" />\n\nOn 22 March the Alpes-Maritimes prefecture issued a decree putting into place a curfew from 10&nbsp;pm to 5&nbsp;am affecting cities of more than 10,000 residents and all towns on the Mediterranean coast until 31 March 2020. This replaced local measures which had already been taken in [[Nice]], [[B\u00e9ziers]], and [[Cannes]].<ref name=\"lexpress2121662\">{{cite web|language=fr|work=L'Express|title=Confinement : Nice, Mulhouse, Perpignan... Ces communes qui ont instaur\u00e9 un couvre-feu |date=23 March 2020|url=https://www.lexpress.fr/actualite/societe/confinement-nice-mulhouse-perpignan-ces-communes-qui-ont-instaure-un-couvre-feu_2121662.html}}</ref>\n\n==== Saint Barth\u00e9lemy ====\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saint Barth\u00e9lemy}}\nA resident of the French island of [[Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]] was diagnosed with COVID-19 on 1 March. His parents on the neighbouring island of [[Saint Martin]] also tested positive.<ref name=\":33\">{{cite web|url=http://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/polynesie/coronavirus-premiers-cas-confirmes-outre-mer-saint-martin-saint-barth-805865.html|title=Coronavirus : premiers cas confirm\u00e9s en Outre-mer, \u00e0 Saint-Martin et Saint-Barth|website=Polyn\u00e9sie la 1\u00e8re|language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302172416/https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/polynesie/coronavirus-premiers-cas-confirmes-outre-mer-saint-martin-saint-barth-805865.html|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== Saint-Martin ====\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Collectivity of Saint Martin}}\nA couple from the French part of [[Saint Martin]] island was diagnosed with COVID-19 on 1 March. Their son, who lives on the neighbouring island of [[Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]], also tested positive.<ref name=\":33\" />\n\n==== French Polynesia ====\n{{Main| 2020 coronavirus pandemic in French Polynesia}}\n[[Maina Sage]], a French politician representing French Polynesia at the [[French national assembly]], was diagnosed with the first case of COVID-19 in [[French Polynesia]] on 11 March.\n\n==== New Caledonia ====\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in New Caledonia}}\n\nAs of 19 March, there have been two cases in New Caledonia.<ref name=\"rnz412092\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/pacific/412092/coronavirus-new-cases-in-tahiti-new-caledonia |title=Coronavirus: New cases in Tahiti, New Caledonia |date=19 March 2020 |work=RNZ |access-date=19 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==Effects on civilian life==\n=== Closures ===\nOn 28 February, the fashion designer [[agn\u00e8s b.]] (not to be confused with [[Agn\u00e8s Buzyn]]) cancelled fashion shows in [[Paris Fashion Week]], which had been scheduled to run until 3 March.<ref name=\"20200228reuters\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-france-fashion-idUSKCN20M23F|title=French fashion label Agnes B cancels Paris show due to coronavirus|date=28 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229025718/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-france-fashion-idUSKCN20M23F|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The following day, the Paris [[half marathon]] scheduled for Sunday 1 March with 44,000 participants was cancelled as one of a number of measures announced by health minister [[Olivier V\u00e9ran]].<ref name=\"20200229washingtontimes\">{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2020/feb/29/paris-half-marathon-canceled-because-of-coronaviru/ |title=Paris half-marathon canceled because of coronavirus |work=[[The Washington Post]] |agency=[[Associated Press]] |date=29 February 2020|accessdate=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229213316/https://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2020/feb/29/paris-half-marathon-canceled-because-of-coronaviru/ |archive-date=29 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March, the [[Ligue de Football Professionnel]] suspended [[Ligue 1]] and [[Ligue 2]] (the top two divisions of football in France) indefinitely due to health risks.<ref name=\"20200313lfp\">{{cite news |url=https://www.lfp.fr/Articles/COMMUNIQU\u00c9S/2020/03/13/communique-de-la-lfp |title=Communiqu\u00e9 de la LFP |publisher=lfp.fr |date=13 March 2020 |accessdate=13 March 2020 |language=fr}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 March, many cultural institutions announced their closure. These are mainly Parisian institutions or institutions in the Paris region, such as [[Louvre]], [[Centre Pompidou|Centre Georges Pompidou]], [[Eiffel Tower]], [[Mus\u00e9e d'Orsay]], or [[Palace of Versailles|Ch\u00e2teau de Versailles]],<ref name=\"francetvinfo3864933\">{{cite web|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/culture/coronavirus-chateau-de-versailles-le-louvre-orsay-l-olympia-le-chatelet-le-theatre-des-chhtmls-elysees-une-avalanche-de-fermetures_3864933.html|title=Coronavirus : Ch\u00e2teau de Versailles, Tour Eiffel, Louvre, Centre Pompidou, Mus\u00e9e d'Orsay, Olympia, Ch\u00e2telet, Th\u00e9\u00e2tre des Champs-Elys\u00e9es... des fermetures en cascade|date=13 March 2020|website=Franceinfo|language=fr|access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref> but also institutions in the provinces such as [[Ch\u00e2teau de Montsoreau-Museum of Contemporary Art|Ch\u00e2teau de Montsoreau \u2013 Museum of Contemporary Art]],<ref name=\"www7324271143\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/pays-de-la-loire/saumur-49400/montsoreau-coronavirus-le-chateau-ferme-a-partir-du-samedi-14-mars-mais-solidaire-953282ee-6534-11ea-9f1d-e73242711437|title=Montsoreau. Coronavirus : le ch\u00e2teau ferm\u00e9 \u00e0 partir du samedi 14 mars|last=ROCHARD|first=Benoit|date=13 March 2020|website=Courrier de l'Ouest|language=fr|access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref> [[CAPC mus\u00e9e d'art contemporain de Bordeaux|CAPC \u2013 Mus\u00e9e d'Art Contemporain de Bordeaux]], [[Museum of European and Mediterranean Civilisations|MUCEM in Marseille]].<ref name=\"laprovence5930600\">{{cite web|url=https://www.laprovence.com/actu/en-direct/5930600/fermeture-mucem.html|title=Marseille : le Mucem ferme ses portes|date=13 March 2020|website=LaProvence.com|language=fr|access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Restrictions on movement===\nAs of 23 March 2020,<ref>[https://www.gov.uk/government/news/french-personal-travel-waiver-certificate World news story French personal travel waiver certificate] ''www.gov.uk'', accessed 4 April 2020</ref> all people are required to complete and carry an ''attestation'' form to leave their homes and can be fined for non-essential journeys.<ref>[https://www.connexionfrance.com/French-news/Man-in-France-jailed-for-flouting-Covid-19-confinement-rules-eight-times-in-five-days Man in France jailed for flouting confinement rules] ''\"A man in northern France has been sentenced to two months in prison for violating confinement rules eight times in five days.\"'' 2 April 2020 ''www.connexionfrance.com'', accessed 4 April 2020</ref> Essential journeys include shopping for food, travelling to work, accessing healthcare, and exercising within 1&nbsp;km of the household.\n\n== Shortage of masks controversy  ==\n{{See also|Shortages related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\nStrategic stocks of masks constituted in 2009 under [[Roselyne Bachelot]], minister of health from May 2007 to November 2010, amounted to 1&nbsp;billion surgical masks and 600 million [[FFP2 mask]]s. Although she had been criticised for overdoing the epidemic preparation, Olivier Veran appeared to vindicate Bachelot's position, saying such stock levels would have been adequate for the situation at hand.<ref name=bfmtv1878500/> A change of prevention doctrine occurred upon recommendation from the General Health Directorate in July 2011, the decision was taken to allow depletion of strategic stocks on the grounds of cost of maintaining the stockpile \u2013 including arbitrating the cost of obsolescence.<ref name=20200323franceinter/><ref name=bfmtv1878500/> Stock of surgical masks and FFP2 masks in late 2019 had dropped to 140 million and zero units respectively.<ref name=bfmtv1878500/>\nThen-health minister [[Agn\u00e8s Buzyn]] declared on 26 January that there would be no shortage of masks in France during the outbreak.<ref name=20200323franceinter>{{cite web|url=https://www.franceinter.fr/societe/penurie-de-masques-les-raisons-d-un-scandale-d-etat|title=P\u00e9nurie de masques : les raisons d'un 'scandale d'\u00c9tat'|trans-title=Mask shortage: the reasons for the 'state scandal' |date=23 March 2020|website=franceinter.fr}}</ref>\nHowever, the assertion turned out to be incorrect, and health professionals complained that they were ill-equipped to face the impending crisis, as stocks of protective equipment were inadequate.<ref name=20200323franceinter/> On 3 March, with France still facing a shortage, President Macron commandeered all masks produced and stored in the country for distribution to health professionals and people who had contracted the virus.<ref name=bfmtv1878500>{{cite web|url=https://www.bfmtv.com/sante/penurie-de-masques-pourquoi-la-france-avait-decide-de-ne-pas-renouveler-ses-stocks-il-y-a-neuf-ans-1878500.html|title=P\u00e9nurie de masques: pourquoi la France avait d\u00e9cid\u00e9 de ne pas renouveler ses stocks il y a neuf ans |trans-title=Mask shortage: Why did France decide to not maintain its stocks nine years ago |publisher=BFMTV}}</ref><ref name=nouvelobs20200303>{{cite web|url=https://www.nouvelobs.com/coronavirus-de-wuhan/20200303.OBS25572/l-etat-requisitionne-les-stocks-de-masques-de-protection.html|title=L\u2019Etat r\u00e9quisitionne les stocks de masques de protection|trans-title=French government commandeers stocks of protective masks |website=L'Obs}}</ref> The French export ban caused diplomatic tensions as the stocks of masks in France held by a Swedish supplier destined for other countries including Spain and Italy were also seized.<ref name=irishtimes4216184>{{cite web|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/world/europe/coronavirus-european-solidarity-sidelined-as-french-interests-take-priority-1.4216184|title=Coronavirus: European solidarity sidelined as French interests take priority|first=Lara Marlowe Paris|last=Correspondent|website=The Irish Times}}</ref>\n\n== Chloroquine controversy ==\nOn 17 March 2020, [[Didier Raoult]] of the Mediterranean infectious and tropical disease institute in Marseille announced in a YouTube video entitled \"Coronavirus: endgame!\u201d that a trial by his team involving 24 patients supported the claim that [[hydroxychloroquine]] and [[azithromycin]] were effective in treating COVID-19.<ref name=irishtimes4210278>{{cite web|author=Lara Marlowe |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/world/europe/coronavirus-france-hoping-unorthodox-virologist-can-save-world-1.4210278 |title=Coronavirus: France hoping unorthodox virologist can save world |work=The Irish Times |date=4 January 2020 |accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.connexionfrance.com/French-news/French-researcher-in-Marseille-posts-successful-Covid-19-coronavirus-drug-trial-results|title=French researcher posts successful Covid-19 drug trial|last=France|first=Connexion|website=connexionfrance.com|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref> The design of the study as well as its conclusions are controversial and generally viewed as flawed and inconclusive.<ref name=yahoo024459686>{{cite web|last=Braun |first=Elisa |url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/france-controversial-doctor-stirs-coronavirus-024459686.html |title=In France, controversial doctor stirs coronavirus debate |publisher=Yahoo! Finance |date=n.d.|accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref> Raoult has nevertheless offered testing of potential sufferers at his institute and prescription of hydroxychloroquine to those who tested positive.<ref name=yahoo024459686/> The French Health Minister, [[Olivier V\u00e9ran]], announced that \"new tests will now go ahead to evaluate the results of Raoult, to independently replicate the trials and ensure the findings are scientifically robust, before any possible decision might be made to roll any treatment out to the wider public\".<ref name=connexionfrance0>{{cite web|url=https://www.connexionfrance.com/French-news/French-lab-Sanofi-hypothetically-offers-millions-of-doses-of-potential-Covid-19-Plaquenil-anti-malaria-drug|title=French lab offers \u2018millions of doses\u2019 of Covid-19 drug|website=connexionfrance.com|access-date=19 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=aa.com1770571>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/europe/france-sanofi-offers-potential-drug-to-beat-covid-19/1770571 |title=France: Sanofi offers potential drug to beat COVID-19 |publisher=Aa.com.tr |date=n.d.|accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref> \nOn 30 March, hospitals reported that there had been two dozen cases with three deaths of individuals who were suspected of self-medication with Plaqu\u00e9nil \u2013 branded name for Chloroquine. Drug safety agency (ANSM) warned against potentially fatal side effects, notably cardiac arrhythmia and heart attack. The agency banned use outside of hospitals, even on prescriptions, clinical trials, and stepped up surveillance.<ref name=france2420200331>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200331-french-watchdog-warns-of-dangerous-side-effects-of-unproven-covid-19-coronavirus-treatments |title=French watchdog warns of dangerous side effects of unproven COVID-19 treatments |publisher=France 24 |date=n.d.|accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=france2420200331/>\n \n[[Sanofi]], manufacturer of Plaqu\u00e9nil, offered French authorities millions of doses of the drug for use against COVID-19.<ref name=aa.com1770571/>\n\n==Cooperation with neighbouring states==\nOn 29 February 2020, Monaco announced the first COVID-19 case, a man who was admitted to the [[Princess Grace Hospital Centre]], then transferred to Nice University Hospital in France.<ref name=\":37\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bfmtv.com/sante/coronavirus-un-premier-cas-de-contamination-detecte-a-monaco-et-transfere-au-chu-de-nice-1866392.html|title=Coronavirus: un premier cas de contamination d\u00e9tect\u00e9 \u00e0 Monaco et transf\u00e9r\u00e9 au CHU de Nice|last=BFMTV|publisher=BFMTV|language=fr|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229112259/https://www.bfmtv.com/sante/coronavirus-un-premier-cas-de-contamination-detecte-a-monaco-et-transfere-au-chu-de-nice-1866392.html|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Also on 29 February 2020, three French nationals and one Italian resident of [[Ain]] were being hospitalised in [[Lausanne]] or other places in [[Switzerland]].<ref name=\"ledauphine.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ledauphine.com/sante/2020/02/29/coronavirus-depuis-sa-chambre-d-hopital-a-annecy-pour-moi-il-n-y-a-pas-de-danger|title=Haute-Savoie. Coronavirus : depuis sa chambre d'h\u00f4pital \u00e0 Annecy, \"pour moi il n'y a pas de danger\"|website=ledauphine.com|language=fr|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229113051/https://www.ledauphine.com/sante/2020/02/29/coronavirus-depuis-sa-chambre-d-hopital-a-annecy-pour-moi-il-n-y-a-pas-de-danger|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"ledauphine.com\"/>\n\nOn 22 March 2020, Switzerland announced that three hospitals near the Alsace region have agreed to take in any French-based patients after Alsace officials made a request for assistance.<ref name=\"swissinfo45634674\">{{cite web |last1=Bally |first1=Gaetan |title=Swiss hospitals to take French coronavirus patients |url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/cross-border-care_swiss-hospitals-take-french-coronavirus-patients/45634674 |website=swissinfo.ch |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=fr |date=22 March 2020}}</ref> Patients from Grand Est were also taken into hospitals in [[Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg]], [[:Rhineland-Palatinate]], [[Saarland]] and [[Hesse]] in Germany.\n\nUp to 1 April 2020 over 100 COVID-19 patients from Alsace had been transferred for treatment to Germany, [[Luxembourg]] and Switzerland.<ref>[https://www.nzz.ch/schweiz/coronavirus-so-kam-frankreich-zu-den-schweizer-spitalplaetzen-ld.1549263 Antonio Fumagalli: \"So kam Frankreich zu den Pl\u00e4tzen auf Schweizer Intensivstationen \u2013 im Gegensatz zu Italien\"] [[Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung]] 1 April 2020</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n\n(Source: official daily statistics from Minister of Health <ref name=\"dashboard Covid19 France\" />)\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|colors=#F46D43\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=600\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|x=25 Feb, 26 Feb, 27 Feb, 28 Feb, 29 Feb, 1 Mar, 2 Mar, 3 Mar, 4 Mar, 5 Mar, 6 Mar, 7 Mar, 8 Mar, 9 Mar, 10 Mar, 11 Mar, 12 Mar, 13 Mar, 14 Mar, 15 Mar, 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar, 21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 25 Mar, 26 Mar, 27 Mar, 28 Mar, 29 Mar, 30 Mar, 31 Mar, 1 Apr, 2 Apr, 3 Apr, 4 Apr, 5 Apr, 6 Apr\n|yAxisTitle=No. of cases\n|legend=Legend\n|y1= 13, 18, 38, 57, 100, 130, 191, 212, 285, 423, 613, 949, 1126, 1412, 1784, 2281, 2876, 3661, 4491, 5423, 6633, 7730, 9134, 10995, 12612, 14459, 16689, 19856, 22302, 25233, 29155, 32964, 37575, 40174, 44550, 52128, 56989, 59105, 64338, 68605, 70478, 74390\n|y1Title=Total No. of cases\n|yGrid= |xGrid= \n}}\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|width=600\n|colors=#F46D43\n|showValues=offset:2\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|type=rect\n|x=25 Feb, 26 Feb, 27 Feb, 