OUEST-FRANCE. Coronavirus : un premier cas d\u00e9tect\u00e9 \u00e0 Rennes, une femme de pompier hospitalis\u00e9e|last=GRISOT|first=Paul|date=29 February 2020|website=Ouest-France|language=fr|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229172658/https://www.ouest-france.fr/sante/virus/coronavirus/info-ouest-france-coronavirus-un-premier-cas-detecte-rennes-une-femme-de-pompier-hospitalisee-6758739|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Morbihan]],<ref name=\":35\" /> [[Haut-Rhin]],<ref name=\"auto4\" /> [[Eure]],<ref name=\"auto5\" /> [[Sarthe]],<ref name=\"auto3\" /> [[Gard]],<ref name=\":38\" /> [[Dr\u00f4me]],<ref name=\":39\" /> [[Sa\u00f4ne-et-Loire]],<ref name=\":40\" /> all the departments of the region [[Hauts-de-France]], except the [[Nord (French department)|Nord]],<ref name=\"20minutes2730587\">{{cite web|url=https://www.20minutes.fr/sante/2730587-20200302-coronavirus-covid-19-desormais-present-toute-region-hauts-france|title=Le coronavirus est d\u00e9sormais pr\u00e9sent dans tous les Hauts-de-France|website=20 Minutes|language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302172701/https://www.20minutes.fr/sante/2730587-20200302-coronavirus-covid-19-desormais-present-toute-region-hauts-france|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and in the overseas territories of [[Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]] and [[Collectivity of Saint Martin|Saint Martin]].<ref name=\":33\" />\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/France medical cases}}\n\n== Simulation statistics ==\nSimulation studies helped convince the government that taking no action would result in large numbers of civilian casualties. In such a case between 30,000 and 100,000 more [[Intensive care unit|ICU]] beds would be required in the hospitals. In France there are 5,000 ''[[:fr:Service de r\u00e9animation|r\u00e9animation]]'' beds and 7,364 ICU beds.\nThis simulation was provided by [[Neil Ferguson (epidemiologist)|Neil Ferguson]], epidemiologist at the [[Imperial College London]].<ref name=\"lemonde6033149\">[https://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2020/03/15/coronavirus-les-simulations-alarmantes-des-epidemiologistes-pour-la-france_6033149_3244.html Coronavirus : les simulations alarmantes des \u00e9pid\u00e9miologistes pour la France] 15 March 2020 ''Le Monde''. Retrieved 15 March 2020</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on aviation]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on education]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on religion]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on politics]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on television]]\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|COVID-19 pandemic in France}}\n* Data and maps, frequently updated:\n** {{cite web |url=https://coronavirus-global.com/france |title=Coronavirus France updates and news |trans-title=Latest news and statistics of coronavirus in France. |access-date=4 April 2020 |language=English, French, Spanish, Portuguese, German, Italian, Swedish, Norwegian, Finnish, Estonian, Russian}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in France}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|France|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n{{#related:Emmanuel Macron}}\n{{#related:\u00c9douard Philippe}}\n{{#related:2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in France| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|France]]\n[[Category:January 2020 events in France]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in France]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in France]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in France]]\n", "name_user": "The wub", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:refs after punctuat