{"title_page": "Footscray RUFC", "text_new": "{{Refimprove|date=May 2013}}\n\n{{Infobox rugby team\n| teamname       = Footscray RUFC\n| image          = \n| imagesize      = \n| union          = [[Kent Rugby Football Union|Kent RFU]], [[Middlesex Rugby Football Union|Middlesex RFU]]\n| fullname       = Footscray Rugby Union Football Club\n| nickname       =  \n| shortname      = \n| countryflag    = ENG\n| countryflagvar = \n| founded        = {{Start date and age|df=yes|1967}}\n| region         = \n| location       = [[New Eltham]], [[Royal Borough of Greenwich|Greenwich]], [[London]], [[England]]\n| ground         = Footscray Playing Fields\n| capacity       = \n| chairman       = Dicky Bunton\n| ceo            =Chris Jones \n| president      = Barry Lewis\n| captain        = Kelvin Munroe \n| top scorer     =Jimmy Wilcox  \n| caps           =  \n| coach          =Sam \u201cTHE BOY\u201d Leese \n| url            = http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/footscrayrufc\n| league         = [[Shepherd Neame Kent 2|Kent 1]]\n| season         = 2020-21\n| position       = Relegated from [[Shepherd Neame Kent 1|Kent 1]] (10th)\n}}\n\n'''Footscray RUFC''' is a [[rugby union]] club based in [[New Eltham]], South East [[London]]. The club has three men's teams, a women's team and a mini rugby section. \n\nThe club was formed in 1967 by workers at the [[Kolster-Brandes]] (later [[ITT Corporation|ITT]], and then [[Standard Telephones and Cables|STC]]) Factory in [[Foots Cray]], Kent. In the early 90s, STC closed the Foots Cray site and the side became homeless, playing home games at a local school for a period. The club moved to New Eltham in 1995.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kent|first=Dan|title=Footscray website|url=http://www.footscrayrufc.co.uk/}}</ref>\n\nThe club hosts the annual Footscray 7s tournament on the first Saturday in May. The [[rugby sevens]] tournament attracts high quality entrants from across the country.\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Kent Rugby Football Union|Kent RFU]]\n*[[Middlesex Rugby Football Union|Middlesex RFU]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rugby union in England}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Footscray Rufc}}\n[[Category:English rugby union teams]]\n[[Category:Rugby union in Kent]]\n[[Category:1967 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Rugby clubs established in 1967]]\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=May 2013}}\n\n{{Infobox rugby team\n| teamname       = Footscray\n| image          = \n| imagesize      = \n| union          = [[Kent Rugby Football Union|Kent RFU]], [[Middlesex Rugby Football Union|Middlesex RFU]]\n| fullname       = Footscray Rugby Union Football Club\n| nickname       =  \n| shortname      = \n| countryflag    = ENG\n| countryflagvar = \n| founded        = {{Start date and age|df=yes|1967}}\n| region         = \n| location       = [[New Eltham]], [[Royal Borough of Greenwich|Greenwich]], [[London]], [[England]]\n| ground         = Footscray Playing Fields\n| capacity       = \n| chairman       = Dan Kent\n| ceo            = \n| president      = Barry Lewis\n| captain        = Gary Lansdale \n| top scorer     =  \n| caps           =  \n| coach          = \n| url            = http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/footscrayrufc\n| league         = [[Shepherd Neame Kent 2|Kent 2]]\n| season         = 2018\u201319\n| position       = Relegated from [[Shepherd Neame Kent 1|Kent 1]] (10th)\n}}\n\n'''Footscray RUFC''' is a [[rugby union]] club based in [[New Eltham]], South East [[London]]. The club has three men's teams, a women's team and a mini rugby section. \n\nThe club was formed in 1967 by workers at the [[Kolster-Brandes]] (later [[ITT Corporation|ITT]], and then [[Standard Telephones and Cables|STC]]) Factory in [[Foots Cray]], Kent. In the early 90s, STC closed the Foots Cray site and the side became homeless, playing home games at a local school for a period. The club moved to New Eltham in 1995.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kent|first=Dan|title=Footscray website|url=http://www.footscrayrufc.co.uk/}}</ref>\n\nThe club hosts the annual Footscray 7s tournament on the first Saturday in May. The [[rugby sevens]] tournament attracts high quality entrants from across the country.\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Kent Rugby Football Union|Kent RFU]]\n*[[Middlesex Rugby Football Union|Middlesex RFU]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rugby union in England}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Footscray Rufc}}\n[[Category:English rugby union teams]]\n[[Category:Rugby union in Kent]]\n[[Category:1967 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Rugby clubs established in 1967]]\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7f:c26d:f000:7d00:6cb2:e7a7:1bc0", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(League)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Footscray_RUFC"}
{"title_page": "Westworld (season 2)", "text_new": "{{short description|Season of television series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox television season\n| season_number    = 2\n| bgcolour         = #9099AE\n| image            = Westworld season 2.png\n| caption          = Blu-ray cover\n| starring         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Evan Rachel Wood]]\n* [[Thandie Newton]]\n* [[Jeffrey Wright]]\n* [[James Marsden]]\n* [[Tessa Thompson]]\n* [[Fares Fares]]\n* [[Luke Hemsworth]]\n* [[Louis Herthum]]\n* [[Simon Quarterman]]\n* [[Talulah Riley]]\n* [[Rodrigo Santoro]]\n* [[Gustaf Skarsg\u00e5rd]]\n* [[Ed Harris]]\n* [[Ingrid Bols\u00f8 Berdal]]\n* [[Clifton Collins Jr.]]\n* [[Angela Sarafyan]]\n* [[Katja Herbers]]\n* [[Shannon Woodward]]\n* [[Anthony Hopkins]]\n* [[Zahn McClarnon]]\n}}\n| country          = United States\n| network          = [[HBO]]\n| first_aired      = {{Start date|2018|4|22}}\n| last_aired       = {{End date|2018|6|24}}\n| num_episodes     = 10\n| episode_list     = Westworld (TV series)#Episodes\n}}\nThe second season of the American [[science fiction]] [[Western (genre)|western]] [[television series]] ''[[Westworld (TV series)|Westworld]]'' (subtitled ''The Door'') premiered on [[HBO]] on April 22, 2018,  and concluded on June 24, 2018, consisting of ten episodes.\n\nThe television series was created by [[Jonathan Nolan]] and [[Lisa Joy]], and it is based on the [[Westworld (film)|1973 film of the same name]], written and directed by [[Michael Crichton]]. The second season stars an ensemble cast led by [[Evan Rachel Wood]], [[Thandie Newton]], [[Jeffrey Wright]], [[James Marsden]], [[Tessa Thompson]], and [[Ed Harris]].\n\nThe second season has received positive reviews from critics.\n\n==Plot==\nAfter killing Dr. Ford from the end of season one, Dolores converts and leads the other hosts in killing many of the other guests in the few weeks that follow. She seeks to find a way to get out of the park to continue her revenge, and knows she must recover her father Peter's \"pearl\" to do so and unlock Westworld's true secrets with it. Charlotte, who was attempting to smuggle Westworld data through Peter, also seeks the host as she cannot call for extraction without that data. Bernard still struggles with the fact he is a host, and comes to learn that Dr. Ford still has significant influence on him and the park. Maeve is aided by Lee and Hector to find her daughter, while learning there are many other parks to Westworld. The Man in Black is forced to come to terms with why he has spent so much time in the park when he encounters his daughter Emily.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{main|List of Westworld characters}}\n===Main===\n{{Div col|colwidth=25em}}\n* [[Evan Rachel Wood]] as Dolores Abernathy<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter.com\">{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/westworld-season-2-all-details-far-1081834|title='Westworld' Season 2: All the Details (So Far)|work=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Josh|last=Wigler|date=February 5, 2018|accessdate=April 14, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Thandie Newton]] as Maeve Millay<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter.com\"/>\n* [[Jeffrey Wright]] as Bernard Lowe / Arnold Weber<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter.com\"/>\n* [[James Marsden]] as Teddy Flood<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ew.com/tv/2018/01/11/james-marsden-westworld-season-2/|title=James Marsden: 'Westworld' season 2 is 'so much bigger'|work=Entertainment Weekly|first=Maureen Lee|last=Lenker|date=January 11, 2018|accessdate=April 14, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Tessa Thompson]] as Charlotte Hale / Dolores Abernathy<ref name=\"digitalspy.com\"/>\n* [[Fares Fares]] as Antoine Costa<ref name=\"Aug2017Casting\"/>{{efn|name=s2|Credited with the main cast in the episodes in which they appear.}}\n* [[Luke Hemsworth]] as Ashley Stubbs<ref name=\"digitalspy.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/westworld/news/a851184/westworld-season-2-cast-tessa-thompson/|title=Westworld announces returning cast for season 2, including Tessa Thompson and more fan-favourites|date=March 1, 2018|work=Digital Spy|first=Justin|last=Harp|accessdate=April 14, 2018}}</ref>{{efn|name=s2}}\n* [[Louis Herthum]] as Peter Abernathy<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/03/westworld-louis-herthum-promoted-series-regular-season-2-hbo-1202052806/|title='Westworld': Louis Herthum Upped To Series Regular For Season 2 On HBO|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 27, 2017|accessdate=April 8, 2017}}</ref>{{efn|name=s2}}\n* [[Simon Quarterman]] as Lee Sizemore<ref name=\"digitalspy.com\"/>{{efn|name=s2}}\n* [[Talulah Riley]] as Angela<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/tv/2017/03/23/westworld-season-2-angela/|title=Westworld season 2 makes Talulah Riley a (very deadly) series regular|last=Hibberd|first=James|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=March 23, 2017|accessdate=March 23, 2017}}</ref>{{efn|name=s2}}\n* [[Rodrigo Santoro]] as Hector Escaton<ref>{{cite web|url=http://westworldwatchers.com/2017/08/14/rodrigo-santoro-confirmed-westworld-season-2/|title=Rodrigo Santoro Confirmed for Westworld Season 2! - Westworld Watchers|date=August 14, 2017|work=Westworld Watchers|first=Dylan|last=Moir|accessdate=April 14, 2018}}</ref>{{efn|name=s2}}\n* [[Gustaf Skarsg\u00e5rd]] as Karl Strand<ref name=\"Aug2017Casting\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/westworld-season-2-cast-1202521782/|title='Westworld' Season 2 Adds Three Actors, Including 'Vikings' Star|work=Variety|first=Joe|last=Otterson|date=August 9, 2017|accessdate=August 10, 2017}}</ref>{{efn|name=s2}}\n* [[Ed Harris]] as William {{a.k.a.}} the Man in Black<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter.com\"/>\n* [[Ingrid Bols\u00f8 Berdal]] as Armistice<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2016/12/05/westworld-season-2-spoilers-interview-ford-dolores-flies/|title=Westworld EPs Dish Dolores' Decision, Ford's Plan, Other Parks and Season 2: 'We're Gonna See a Lot of Flies'|date=December 5, 2016|work=TVLine|first=Kimberly|last=Roots|accessdate=April 